 Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"Secret History of the Italian Crisis,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"The Secret Bull,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Reminiscences of Massimo d'Azeglio,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"The Next General Council,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Ranke,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"M. Littr\u00e9 on the Middle Ages,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Mr. Goldwin Smith on the Political History of England,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Nicholas of Cusa,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Maurice of Saxony,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"The Acta Sanctorum,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"The Queen's Journal,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1868).\n* \"Ozanam on the Fifth Century,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1868).\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3011300;view=1up;seq=42 \"The Massacre of St. Bartholomew,\"] ''The North British Review'' (1868).\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3011300;view=1up;seq=139 \"The Pope and the Council,\"] ''The North British Review'' (1869).\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3011302;view=1up;seq=187 \"The Vatican Council,\"] ''The North British Review'' (1870).\n* [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=uc1.b3011302;view=1up;seq=355 \"The Borgias and their Latest Historian,\"] ''The North British Review'' (1871).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/quarterlyreview01smitgoog#page/n12/mode/2up \"Wolsey and the Divorce of Henry VIII,\"] ''Quarterly Review'' (1877).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/quarterlyreview85smitgoog#page/n124/mode/2up \"Sir Erskine May's 'Democracy in Europe',\"] ''Quarterly Review'' (1878).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/twentiethcentury17londuoft#page/464/mode/2up \"George Eliot's Life,\"] ''The Nineteenth Century'' (1885).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/englishhistorica01londuoft#page/6/mode/2up \"German Schools of History,\"] ''English Historical Review'' (1886).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/englishhistorica05londuoft#page/306/mode/2up \"Wilhelm von Giesebretch,\"] ''English Historical Review'' (1890).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/englishhistorica05londuoft#page/700/mode/2up \"D\u00f6llinger's Historical Work,\"] ''English Historical Review'' (1890).\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Acton Institute for the Study of Religion & Liberty]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==References==\n*{{EB1911||wstitle=Acton (John Emerich Edward Dalberg Acton), 1st Baron |volume=1 |pages=159\u2013160}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Acton | first1 = Harold | authorlink = Harold Acton | year = 1961 | title = Lord Acton | url = | journal = Chicago Review | volume = 15 | issue = 1| pages = 31\u201344 | doi=10.2307/25293642| jstor = 25293642 }}\n* Boyd, Kelly, ed. ''Encyclopedia of Historians and Historical Writers'' (Rutledge, 1999) 1:1-2\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Brinton | first1 = Crane | authorlink = Crane Brinton | year = 1919 | title = Lord Acton's Philosophy of History | journal = The Harvard Theological Review | volume = 12 | issue = 1| pages = 84\u2013112 | jstor=1507914 | doi=10.1017/s0017816000010300| url = https://zenodo.org/record/1428624 }}\n* Chadwick, Owen (1976). ''Acton and Gladstone''. London: Athlone Press. \n* Chadwick, Owen (1998). ''Acton and History''. Cambridge University Press.\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Deane | first1 = Seamus F | year = 1972 | title = Lord Acton and Edmund Burke | url = | journal = Journal of the History of Ideas | volume = 33 | issue = 2| pages = 325\u2013335 | doi=10.2307/2708878| jstor = 2708878 }}\n* [[Mary Gladstone|Drew, Mary Gladstone]] (1924). [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015063782596;view=1up;seq=13 \"Acton and Gladstone.\"] In: ''Acton, Gladstone, and Others.'' London, Nisbet & Co., ltd., pp.&nbsp;1\u201331.\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Engel-Janosi | first1 = Friedrich | year = 1941 | title = Reflections of Lord Acton on Historical Principles | url = | journal = The Catholic Historical Review | volume = 27 | issue = 2| pages = 166\u2013185 }}\n* F